title: Raiffeisenlandesbank Oberösterreich (RLB OÖ) - Silver Sponsor of PyCon DE & PyData
---
full_description: The Raiffeisenlandesbank Oberösterreich (RLB OÖ) is the fifth-largest bank in Austria, with consolidated total assets of 49 billion euros. With an extensive portfolio of equity investments and 64 Raiffeisen banks comprising 345 branches in Upper Austria, RLB OÖ forms a stable triangle that actively shapes the regional economy and provides key impulses both within the region and throughout Austria. Beyond Upper Austria, the bank operates in Salzburg, Vienna and in southern Germany through branch offices. It also maintains a global network of partner banks, enabling it to support its customers worldwide.
As a bank, data and analytics have always been at the core of our business. That’s why Python is a fundamental tool for our data enthusiasts. For many years, we have used Python for data preparation, visualization, and classical machine learning, empowering us to analyze complex data, optimize processes, and deliver better services to our customers. With the rise of generative AI, these technologies have gained even more visibility and potential, opening up new opportunities that are at your fingertips if you "speak" Python.

